title: Tropical Mexican Salad with Fish
summary: Tropical Mexican Salad with Fish is a dairy free and pescatarian recipe with 4 servings. One portion of this dish contains about 47g of protein, 34g of fat, and a total of 809 calories. For $5.52 per serving, this recipe covers 48% of your daily requirements of vitamins and minerals. Not a lot of people really liked this main course. This recipe from Yummy Mummy Kitchen has 1 fans. From preparation to the plate, this recipe takes around 45 minutes. This recipe is typical of Mexican cuisine. Head to the store and pick up toss salad greens, panko bread crumbs, corn, and a few other things to make it today. To use up the juice of lime you could follow this main course with the Cranberry-Orange Juice Slushee as a dessert. All things considered, we decided this recipe deserves a spoonacular score of 90%. This score is outstanding. Try Tropical Fish Fillets, Mexican Tropical Chile Brine, and Spicy Fish with Tropical Salsa for similar recipes.

winePairing.pairingText: Mexican on the menu? Try pairing with Pinot Noir, Riesling, and Sparkling rosé. Acidic white wines like riesling or low-tannin reds like pinot noir can work well with Mexican dishes. Sparkling rosé is a safe pairing too. The Foxen Bien Nacido Block Eight Pinot Noir with a 4.1 out of 5 star rating seems like a good match. It costs about 62 dollars per bottle.
